t of the United States If you are a member of the Armed Forces you may apply through your respective branch of service or if you are the child of a deceased or disabled veteran you may apply directly to the Academy of your choice Guidelines Must be at least 17 years of age but not yet 23 years of age A citizen of the United States Unmarried with no legal obligation to support a child or dependent A legal resident of the Second Congressional District You will need to obtain an application packet and submit the following documents to Congressman Carson s office A complete application Three letters of recommendation An official transcript including your Junior year course work your grade point average and class rank A qualified medical examination will be scheduled with the Department of Defense Medical Review Board through the Academy after they receive your pre candidate questionnaire Basis for the nomination Candidate s school record grade point average GPA and class rank include a copy of your senior class schedule also The average competitive candidate is in the upper fifth of his her class Extra curricular activities athletics community service and school organizations SAT or ACT scores A competitive candidate must score above 560 on verbal and 600 on math You are encouraged to retake the SAT if your scores are not at this level Motivation Interview with Congressman Carson s Service Academy Selection Board Academy Application File Application For Service Academy nomination Application For Service Academy nomination pdf Adobe Acrobat Application For Service Academy nomination Application For Service Academy nomination htm HTML Application For Service Academy nomination Application For Service Academy nomination doc MS Word You must also complete the appropriate application process with each Academy of interest to you You must also complete the appropriate application process with each Academy of interest to you If you are interested in applying to an Academy conta